---
description: Canonical Nx/pnpm commands and tag taxonomy for running and building projects.
alwaysApply: true
---

Run everything through Nx from the repo root. Convenience scripts in root `package.json`:

```bash
pnpm timemanager      # nx serve timemanager-api (GraphQL + auth + DB); Flutter via IDE launch.json
pnpm user-manager     # nx run-many -t serve -p user-manager-web,user-manager-api
pnpm db:up            # nx run timemanager-api:migrate (starts Postgres + pgAdmin, then migrates)
pnpm db:down          # nx run timemanager-db:down
```

Direct Nx usage: `nx serve <project>`, `nx build <project>`, `nx run-many -t <target> -p <a,b>`, `nx run <project>:<target>`.

Project tags (in each `project.json`) — use for filtering and to understand scope:

- `scope:*` — `scope:timemanager`, `scope:user-manager`, `scope:shared`
- `type:*` — `type:app`, `type:api`, `type:infra`, `type:lib`
- `runtime:*` — `runtime:flutter`, `runtime:deno`, `runtime:node`

Notes:

- `timemanager-api:migrate` `dependsOn` `timemanager-db:up`; `serve` and `seed` depend on `migrate`, so schema is applied before the API or seed runs.
- `timemanager-api:serve` `dependsOn` `user-manager-api:serve` (continuous), so auth starts with the GraphQL API; Flutter is launched from the IDE (`.vscode/launch.json`).
- Deno and Flutter targets are `nx:run-commands` wrappers (no `@nx/deno` plugin).
- Full workflows (seed, migrations, smoke checks): [.ai/workflows.md](mdc:.ai/workflows.md).
